main event: USAF personnel at Marville Air Force Base reported a radar contact with an unidentified flying object displaying unusual maneuvers and speed on August 16, 1966.
interesting points: The radar detected one object that made rapid maneuvers and exhibited high speeds,The observed maneuvers were considered unusual for conventional aircraft,The radar contact lasted for approximately 40 seconds,The conclusion stated that the object was possibly a false target,The sighting is part of Project Blue Book investigations.
witness description: one USAF officer and one USAF airman
